<h3>Quality Services</h3>
PCHC offers a range of physical therapy services to meet your needs whether rehabilitation, conditioning, training, prevention, or reeducation. We strive to give you the attention you deserve in the treatment or your injury, condition, or therapy concern. Our goal is to assist you in returning to your prior level of function, and we truly believe that physical therapy is both the science of healing and the art of caring.

Services Offered:
<ul>
	<li>Orthopedic Rehabilitation</li>
	<li>Sports Medicine</li>
	<li>Neurological Rehabilitation</li>
	<li>Pediatric Therapy</li>
	<li>Work Hardening/Conditioning</li>
	<li>Orthotics Evaluation &amp; Casting</li>
	<li>Vestibular Rehabilitation</li>
	<li>Gait &amp; Balance Training</li>
	<li>Fall Prevention Programs</li>
	<li>Manual Therapy</li>
	<li>Therapeutic Exercise</li>
	<li>Neuromuscular Reeducation</li>
</ul>
<h3>Caring Staff</h3>
We have a full staff of 12 licensed Physical Therapists with the highest level of training and experience in the field of physical therapy. Each therapist is equipped with the most up-to-date knowledge of effective techniques and treatment options. They will treat your concern with the utmost care and compassion.
<h3>Convenience</h3>
We have flexible scheduling and convenient hours. We are open 6 days a week and offer morning, evening, and weekend hours so you can be sure we are accessible and that your treatment begins as soon as possible. Services are available at 4 convenient locations.

Physical Therapy has proven effective in treating of a number of medical concerns, including: Neck &amp; Back Pain, Arthritis &amp; Joint Pain, Sprains &amp; Strains, Pre &amp; Post Surgical Rehabilitation, Balance &amp; Walking Difficulties, Headaches, TMJ Disorders, Chronic Pain, Fibromyalgia, Dizziness &amp; Vertigo, Multiple Sclerosis, Stroke, and Parkinsonâ€™s Disease.

